### Initial setup on phone


1. Connect mobile

2. Check if USB debugging is enabled

```sh
cd /tmp
adb devices

```

The output should look like this:

```sh
name@computer: /tmp $ adb devices
List of devices attached
TF224JHN5	device
```

### Edit files and create APK

3. Go to https://github.com/sanskrit2020/devanagari_offline_AS

4. Edit/create your files 

```sh
devanagari_offline_AS/app/src/main/assets/
```

5. Click "Commit Changes at the bottom of the page"

6. Once you commit changes it will AUTOMATICALLY COMPILE APK

4. Click on Actions. See screenshot:

5. Click the newest run - 

6. Verify artifacts is green tick mark

7. Download the file devanagiri-offline-debug.apk

8. Open terminal

```sh
cd /tmp
unzip devanagiri-offline-debug.apk.zip
adb install app-debug.apk

```
2. Install NPM packages
```sh
npm install
```
